videos.headline: Alabama storms out of gate with 34-yard rush
videos.description: Alabama RB Damien Harris takes the opening handoff downfield for the 34-yard run.

videos.headline: Alabama forces turnover on downs
videos.description: Shaun Dion Hamilton breaks up the QB run by Deondre Francois to force the turnover early in the first quarter.

videos.headline: Tate makes leaping catch in coverage
videos.description: Deondre Francois finds Auden Tate downfield who makes the leaping catch to set up Florida State in Alabama territory.

videos.headline: Francois finds Tate in the corner to put FSU on the board
videos.description: Deondre Francois throws the corner fade to Auden Tate who makes another leaping catch for the Florida State touchdown.

videos.headline: Hurts connects with Ridley on the 53-yard TD
videos.description: Jalen Hurts lobs it to Calvin Ridley deep downfield for the Crimson Tide touchdown.

videos.headline: Alabama blocks field goal to end 1st half
videos.description: Minkah Fitzpatrick gets a hand on the 37-yard field goal attempt from Ricky Aguayo. Rashaan Evans tries to return it but is tripped up downfield.

videos.headline: Alabama, Florida State in low-scoring affair at half
videos.description: Jalen Hurts finds Calvin Ridley for the Crimson Tide's lone touchdown as they take a three-point lead into the half.

videos.headline: Nick Saban says his team is playing like it's the 1st game
videos.description: Alabama head coach Nick Saban discusses mistakes and inconsistency in his team's first half performance.

videos.headline: Jimbo Fisher feels comfortable with his team's 1st half performance
videos.description: Florida State head coach talks about the last few plays of the first half and how his offense has performed so far.

videos.headline: Davis comes flying in to sack Francois
videos.description: Raekwon Davis uses a swim move to sack Deondre Francois for a third-down stop.

videos.headline: Blocked punt sets up Alabama in red zone
videos.description: Damien Harris runs in untouched to block the Florida State punt.

videos.headline: Saban irate with sideline interference
videos.description: Alabama penalized with sideline interference has Nick Saban angry with his assistant coaches.

videos.headline: Florida State fumbles kickoff return
videos.description: Keith Gavin tries to return a bobbled kickoff near the goal line. Dylan Moses forces the fumble to set up Alabama in the red zone.

videos.headline: Harris powers his way in for an Alabama TD
videos.description: Damien Harris brushes off Florida State defenders on his way to the end zone for a Crimson Tide touchdown.

videos.headline: Wallace picks off the pass from Francois
videos.description: Levi Wallace with the interception from Deondre Francois to set up another Alabama drive in Florida State territory.

videos.headline: Wilson with another Alabama INT
videos.description: Mack Wilson steps in front of the pass from Deondre Francois for the second interception of the game.

videos.headline: Francois injured on a sack
videos.description: Deondre Francois is carted off the field after a sack scrambling away from Robbie Harrison.

videos.headline: Saban knows where his team is at after win over FSU
videos.description: Nick Saban talks about Alabama's second-half performance and how they were able to force mistakes and turnovers against Florida State.

videos.headline: Hurts and Ridley talk about 2nd half performance
videos.description: Jalen Hurts and Calvin Ridley talk about how they were able to contribute to Alabama's turnaround in the second half.

videos.headline: Breaking down Alabama's 24-7 win over Florida State
videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit and Chris Fowler discuss the factors that led to Alabama's strong second half performance against Florida State.

videos.headline: Crimson Tide fueled by shutdown D
videos.description: Alabama holds Florida State scoreless in the second half en route to a dominant opening performance.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Crimson Tide fueled by shutdown D) 2017/9/2 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: FSU's Francois out for season with knee injury
videos.description: Florida State quarterback Deondre Francois is out for the season after suffering a patella tendon injury in his left knee during the Seminoles' season-opening loss to Alabama.

tracking.trackingName: NCF_One-Play (Francois gets carted off after sack) 2017/09/02 ESHEET
